@node "intro" "Introduction"
@next "install"
@prev "Main"
  What is "GetIcon!" ?
  --------------------

Do you know the situation ? You`ve got a file e.g. text file and there`s no
icon around ? Or another situatio, you`ve got a directory full of a same
type of file but with various icons which shows all together an unacceptable
picture ? You want to write scripts ? You want to make difficult operations
with step-by-step-operations ? Okay then and go away...or you stay reading.

GetIcon! will do all the operations which usually force you doing such operations
which I described above. It makes iconhandling much easier and does much more than this.

This program is FREEWARE.

Sure, this program is a little bit old, because first I wrote it for my own,
but then I looked out and saw much tools that do at most the same, but I think
if you want have a cheap tool, so take this. So, if you think, the design is quite
the worst ever, maybe, but as I said it was a *private* tool before, don`t be
very demanding. ;)
@endnode

@node "install" "Installation"
@next "requirements"
@prev "intro"
  Installation
  ------------

There`s an Installer script. Simply doubleclick on the Installer icon.
@endnode

@node "requirements" "Requirements"
@next "discl"
@prev "install"
   Requirements
   ­­­­­­­­­­­­

GetIcon! needs OS2.0 V37 or higher. All functions are available at OS3.x. It
needs also muimaster.library V13 or higher. Icon.mcc required (included in this package).
And last but not least "def_" icons in your "ENVARC:Sys".
@endnode

