@node "gadgets" "Gadgets"
@next "menu"
@prev "author"
   Gadgets
   -------

Because there`s a buildin bubble-help-function,I need not many words to
explain,I wrote this program very user-transparent,so that much things
are self-explaining.

The most important things you have to know:
   - look at the both listfields in the upper part of the window
     the left ones is for available "def_"-icons,right ones for your
     files and directories,the so-called "fileslist".

   - you can`t do much wrong,the only thing you have to keep an eye
     are files which already possesses an own icon,these could be
     overwritten ! There will appear a warning before you do that,so you
     can break the operation.

As you can see it`s a quite safe program :-)

Gadget functions listed:

   Update icons   - in case your ENVARC:Sys wins new icons
                    click here to actualize.

   Icon?          - if your are interested in the view of the icon you want use:
                    Click here,a little window will open and will show
                    you the icon image, you can click it like at the WB,
                    if you get enough of that,
                    click "Continue"-button to close the window.

   Info           - if you`ve got OS3.x, this button will be enabled,and
                    after pressing this button,you will get the same
                    like calling the menu point "Information" at the
                    "Icon" menu on the WB. OS2.x users can only get an
                    excusement from me. A replacement has been thrown away
                    and I didn`t want invent the wheel twice.

   Delete         - Remove selected entry/ies from files list

   "Load"-image   - If you don`t want to use "Drag`n`Drop" click here or
                    press "l",after doing that, a filerequester will pop up,
                    choose one or more files or choose one directory.
                    Because of the physics of "asl.library" you can only
                    one directory but much files as you want.

  Type-cyclegadget- Choose also a new type for the target icon,of course
                    only if you want ! WARNING! Datas won`t probably be
                    lost,but the results would become strange,eg. if you
                    make an "Drawer" to a "Tool" ! I hope you know what
                    I mean....

Copy icon position - If a file has got already an icon,but it should
                     get a new ones,position will change sometimes.
                     If this option is set, it means your icon
                     may get a new position,it doesn`t matter,where
                     it will be its new position. If the option is unset,
                     your icon will hold its old position.

   Change type     - Change a type of an icon immediately,in contrast to
                     to the "Start" gadget,it will only change the icon
                     type. Use type-cyclegadget for type-choice. WARNING!
                     The type changing starts immediately after pressing,
                     but before it will appear a requester which will ask you if
                     you really want to do that. I think the damage in
                     case of mischoice will be very small because you can
                     always change it anew. Typechange means not killing
                     files or directory,or changing directory in file or
                     whatever,it simply changes the type of the icon.
                     It will only get a new behaviour when you click,
                     and it`s only important for the OS not for your
                     datas on drive.

   Start           - The right selected entry will be new "iconized",
                     and if wished: new "typed".

   Hide            - Iconify the application,all windows will close,
                     and an appicon appears on WB. Drag your files or
                     directories over it and let them drop there.
                     They will be ordered automatically into the fileslist.
   Quit            - Quit your program here.
@endnode

@node "menu" "Menu"

   Menu
   ----

The menu functions are quite the same like gadget functions.

Project -------
   About     -  About this program.A requester appears.Test it...
   About MUI -  About MUI. A SASG requester appears. Test it..

   Hide      -  Works like the gadget @{"Hide" link "gadgets" 87}
   Quit      -  Works like the gadget @{"Quit" link "gadgets" 91}

Files list ----------
   Update "def_"-list - Works like the gadget @{"Update icons." link "gadgets" 22}
   Add file(s) to list- Works like the gadget @{"'Load' image." link "gadgets" 48}
   Delete entry       - Works like the gadget @{"Delete." link "gadgets" 49}
   Information...     - Works like the gadget @{"Info." link "gadgets" 35}
   Copy icon position - Works like the gadget @{"Copy icon position." link "gadgets" 63}
@endnode

@node "commodity" "Commodity"
   Commodity
   ---------

You can use "Exchange" as navigator !

  Active   - makes "GetIcon!" awake.
  Inactive - makes it asleep.That means it sleeps,inputs will be blocked
             a sleeping pointer appears when you click into the window.
             Maybe this does not make much sense if it is not iconified :)
  Show Interface - Window will be opened
  Hide Interface - Window will be closed,an appicon appears.
  Remove         - The program quits

Use @{"tooltypes" link "tooltypes" 0} to edit your popup-options: - popkey,priority and popup-behaviour.
@endnode

@node "app" "App"

   App
   ---

The right listfield is an app object,that means you can drop there your files
and directories you want to "iconize". The files will automatically ordered
into the list.

If the application is iconified,and an appicon has been appeared, you can also drop here
your files or directories.
@endnode

@node "arexx" "ARexx"
   ARexx
   -----

The ARexx command set is not the greatest. Maybe in the future something will
change...

Name of the Arexx-Port: "GETICON!"

SLEEP

   FUNCTION
    Forces the application to iconify.

   INPUTS
      None

   RESULTS
      None

   SEE ALSO
      WAKEUP

  -----------------------------------

WAKEUP

   FUNCTION
      Forces the application to uniconify.

   INPUTS
      None

   RESULTS
      None

   SEE ALSO
      SLEEP

  -----------------------------------

QUIT

   FUNCTION
      Forces the program to quit.

   INPUTS
      None

   RESULTS
      None

   SEE ALSO

  -----------------------------------

UPDATEDEFS

   FUNCTION
      Updates the "def_" iconlist.

   INPUTS
      None

   RESULTS
      None

   SEE ALSO

  ------------------------------------

ACTION

   FUNCTION
      Starts "iconizing" and "typing" the actual selected entry/ies.
      Yes, I know, without parameters its quite sensless...

   INPUTS
      None

   RESULTS
      None

   SEE ALSO
@endnode

@node "tooltypes" "Tooltypes"

   Tooltypes
   ---------
   
The tooltypes are the standard commodities tooltypes, for popping up or not,
priority and popkey combination.   

CX_POPUP 
  
  INPUTS
    YES = the window popups immediately after start
    NO  = the window does not popup after start, if you set the preferences,
          an appicon will appear
          
  RESULTS
    None
    
  SEE ALSO
  ------------------------------------

CX_POPKEY

  INPUTS
    a keyboard combination like "lalt shift g"  
  
  RESULTS
    None
  
  SEE ALSO
  ------------------------------------
  
CX_PRIORITY
  
  INPUTS
    a priority value

  RESULTS    
    None
  
  SEE ALSO
  ------------------------------------                           
@endnode
